# Changelog

## 0.3.0 (2025-12-29)

- Game was renamed to Project: Idle Takeover from Cyberiada
- Configs validation has been added
- Hotkeys can be now changed
- Updated UI
- Reworked story progression
- Contracts and primary activity are available
- Factions are available
- Items were reworked
- New and changed parameters:
- - Faction influence, replaced district tier points, used to unlock and improve districts
- - Rewards now separate for each district. They now affect process completion speed and shared experience.
- Formulas for parameters were changed
- New programs:
- - Predictive computator, to increase process completion speed
- - Contract autostarter, to start contracts automatically
- New sidejobs:
- - Mainframe relay, to speed up process completion speed
- - Feed analyzer, to improve clones shared experience
- New contracts:
- - Security, basic contract
- - Backroom deal, WSA specific upgrade to gain reward

## 0.2.1 (2025-07-26)

- Fixed various issues
- Added hotkey support

## 0.2 (2025-05-25)

- Added support for factions
- City page is updated, now it shows available sidejobs and information about districts
- Clone page is added, clones can be purchased here and assigned to sidejobs. Sidejobs give constant rewards
- New parameters:
- - Code base, improves mainframe programs price multiplier
- - Connectivity, unlocks better sidejobs and contracts
- - Rewards, improves rewards
- - District tier points, improves rewards from district
- New programs:
- - Circuit designer, increases computational base points
- - Information collector, increases connectivity points
- - Deal maker, increases reward points
- - Clone level autoupgrader, upgrades clones levels
- - Peer reviewer, increases clones experience
- New Overview page to see overall progress
- - Removed available goals icon from top bar, remade as story tab in overview
- - Reworked unlocked features, moved unlocked features tab from statistics to overview
- Removed history API integration
- Updated UI, performance fixes

## 0.1.3 (2025-02-22)

- UI and mobile version bugfixes

## 0.1.2 (2025-01-26)

- UI reworked to be more mobile friendly
- Translations are more optimized, removed excessive JSON conversion
- New sortable list component to allow drag'n'drop without fixed height of list elements
- History support to allow moving back on mobile
- Message log now is on separate page, messages are shown as toasts
- New formatters
- Autosave on leaving game

## 0.1.1 (2024-12-15)

- When game tab is inactive and game is not paused, time will be spent immediately instead of being accumulated
- Added "Buy all" buttons for mainframe programs and hardware tabs
- Reworked programs and processes descriptions. They now can show difference between old and new versions
- Added version migrator
- New alerts to show added offline time and warn about new version

## 0.1 (2024-12-03)

- Mainframe page
- Foundation for the rest of the game: state, UI, settings, alerts, notifications, etc.
- Prototype map generator